{"parse":{"title":"Thematic coherence","pageid":25912881,"revid":860150302,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Developmental_psychology\" title=\"Developmental psychology\">developmental psychology</a>, <b>thematic coherence</b> is an organization of a set of meanings in and through an event.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bloome_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bloome-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> In <a href=\"/wiki/Education\" title=\"Education\">education</a>, for example, the thematic coherence happens when a child during a classroom session understands what all the talking is about.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bloome_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bloome-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>This expression was termed by Habermas and Bluck (2000),<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> along with other terms such as <i>temporal coherence</i>, <i>biographical coherence</i>, and <i>causal coherence</i>, to describe the coherence that people talk about while narrating their own personal experiences (the many different episodes in their life, most especially in childhood and adolescence) which need to be structured within a <a href=\"/wiki/Context_principle\" title=\"Context principle\">context</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Conversation\" title=\"Conversation\">conversation</a> \u2014 although this technique also can be found in literature \u2014 the thematic coherence is when a person (or character) \"is able to derive a general theme or principle about the self based on a narrated sequence of events.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-McAdams_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-McAdams-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thematic_coherence&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Child_development\" title=\"Child development\">Child development</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Developmental_psychology\" title=\"Developmental psychology\">Developmental psychology</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Centration\" title=\"Centration\">Centration</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Private_speech\" title=\"Private speech\">Private speech</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Speech_perception\" title=\"Speech perception\">Speech perception</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Speech_repetition\" title=\"Speech repetition\">Speech repetition</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thematic_coherence&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-bloome-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-bloome_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-bloome_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFBloome2004\" class=\"citation\">Bloome;  et al. (2004), <i>Discourse analysis &amp; the study of classroom language &amp; literacy events: a microethnographic perspective</i>, Routledge, p.&#160;33, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8058-5320-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-8058-5320-9\">978-0-8058-5320-9</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Discourse+analysis+%26+the+study+of+classroom+language+%26+literacy+events%3A+a+microethnographic+perspective&amp;rft.pages=33&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-8058-5320-9&amp;rft.au=Bloome&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThematic+coherence\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFHabermasBluck2000\" class=\"citation\">Habermas, T; Bluck, 2 (2000), \"Getting a life: The development of the life story in adolescence\", <i>Psychological Bulletin</i>, <b>126</b>: 748\u2013769</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Psychological+Bulletin&amp;rft.atitle=Getting+a+life%3A+The+development+of+the+life+story+in+adolescence&amp;rft.volume=126&amp;rft.pages=748-769&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.aulast=Habermas&amp;rft.aufirst=T&amp;rft.au=Bluck%2C+2&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThematic+coherence\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFFivushHaden2003\" class=\"citation\">Fivush, Robyn; Haden, Catherine A (2003), <i>Autobiographical memory and the construction of a narrative self: developmental and cultural perspectives</i>, Routledge, p.&#160;192, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8058-3756-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-8058-3756-8\">978-0-8058-3756-8</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Autobiographical+memory+and+the+construction+of+a+narrative+self%3A+developmenta